==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: kitambilla
<hw>kitambilla</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small shrubby spiny
tree (<spn>Dovyalis hebecarpa</spn>) cultivated for its maroon-purple
fruit with sweet purple pulp tasking like gooseberries; it is native to
Sri Lanka and India.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ketembilla, kitembilla, ketembilla tree, Ceylon
gooseberry, <spn>Dovyalis hebecarpa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A maroon-purple gooseberrylike fruit of India having
a tart-sweet purple pulp used especially for preserves.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ketembilla, kitembilla.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>kitbag</ent>⟦br⟧
